---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import LinkBtn from "../components/LinkBtn.astro";
import { SITE } from "../consts";

const updated = "July 16, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="How this site handles your data: what is collected, why, and your rights."
>
  <article class="flex flex-col gap-8">
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
      <h1 class="font-theme_bold text-3xl text-head_text sm:text-4xl slg:text-5xl">
        Privacy policy<span class="text-link_text_hover">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-p_text">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </section>

    <div class="text-content max-w-3xl text-sm leading-relaxed slg:text-base">
      <p>
        This is the personal portfolio of {SITE.name}. I keep data collection to the minimum needed
        to run the site and answer your messages. This page explains what is collected and why.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-theme_bold text-xl text-head_text">Contact form</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit the contact form, your name, email address and message are delivered to my
        inbox through <LinkBtn link="https://web3forms.com">Web3Forms</LinkBtn>, a form-delivery
        service. I use this information only to reply to you. It is not added to any mailing list
        and never sold or shared.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-theme_bold text-xl text-head_text">Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        The site uses Google Analytics to understand which pages are visited. Google Analytics sets
        cookies and processes your IP address; you can opt out with the
        <LinkBtn link="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout">Google Analytics opt-out add-on</LinkBtn>
        or by blocking cookies in your browser. No analytics data is used for advertising.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-theme_bold text-xl text-head_text">Third-party links</h2>
      <p>
        Booking a call happens on Calendly, and links to GitHub, Upwork, LinkedIn, WhatsApp and
        similar services take you to those platforms. Each has its own privacy policy that applies
        once you are there.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-theme_bold text-xl text-head_text">Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You can ask me at any time to access, correct or delete any personal data I hold about you
        (in practice: your emails and form submissions). Write to
        <LinkBtn link={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</LinkBtn> and I'll take care of it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
